    <body>
      <head>Emil Hatschek</head>
      <div>

        <p>Husband of <ref cRef="entity-003920">Hella (Helena) Schiff</ref> (younger sister of <ref
            cRef="entity-000771">Jeanette Schenker</ref>). The couple had one child:
          <ref cRef="entity-005060">Lotte</ref>.</p>

        <p>Emil was the son of Alexander and Amalie Hatschek (<hi rend="italic">née</hi> Steiner),
          the fifth of six children. He was brought up in Prostějov, near Olomouc (Ollmütz), in
          Moravia (after 1918 in Czechoslovakia). He is briefly mentioned in the correspondence from
            <ref cRef="entity-003920">Hella</ref>’s elder sister <ref cRef="entity-000944">Rosa
            Weil</ref> to <ref cRef="entity-000771">Jeanette Schenker</ref>, including her refence
          to him as a “Lump” (“idiot”) (<ref type="correspondence" cRef="OJ-14-10_15">OJ 14/10,
            [15]</ref>, November 28, 1934), and her reporting of his death (<ref
            type="correspondence" cRef="OJ-14-10_31">OJ 14/10, [31]</ref>). He is unmentioned in
            <ref cRef="entity-000632">Heinrich Schenker</ref>’s diary. He was still living in
          Prostějov at the time of his death. <ref cRef="entity-003920">Hella</ref> outlived him,
          and died in the Holocaust in 1941.</p>
      </div>
